      fullDef: 'Monitoring contracts historically ran 3 years with steep cancellation clauses — 75–100% of the remaining balance. ADT\'s standard contract, for example, commits homeowners to 36 months at $45–$60/month; early termination before month 12 costs 75% of remaining payments, which can exceed $1,000. This model has faced regulatory scrutiny in several states, and class action settlements have resulted in disclosure requirement changes.\n\nThe market has shifted significantly toward month-to-month contracts since Ring Alarm (2018) and SimpliSafe\'s no-contract model demonstrated consumer demand. Month-to-month plans typically cost $5–$15/month more than equivalent long-term contract rates. DIY brands (Ring, Abode, SimpliSafe) almost exclusively offer monthly plans; traditional dealers (ADT, Vivint, Brinks) still favor 3-year terms for subsidized equipment.\n\nBefore signing any contract, read the escalation clause (annual rate increases are often permitted, commonly 3–5%), the relocation policy (can you take the system to a new address, and at what cost), and the equipment ownership terms (leased equipment must be returned or paid off at cancellation).',
