      fullDef: 'Traditional alarm companies like Vivint and ADT frequently offer equipment at $0 upfront by rolling the hardware cost into a 3–5 year monitoring contract. The monthly fee includes both the service and an implicit equipment amortization. At the end of the contract, the customer may not own the equipment — Vivint contracts, for example, specify the equipment is leased and must be returned or paid for at termination.\n\nPurchase-to-own models — either paying upfront ($200–$1,000+ for a full system) or through financing — give the homeowner outright title to the hardware. When moving, purchased equipment can be reinstalled at the new home. DIY systems (Ring, SimpliSafe, Arlo) are almost always sold outright at retail.\n\nOver a 5-year period, the total cost of a leased system (ADT, Vivint) commonly runs $2,500–$4,000 including monitoring. A purchased DIY system with professional monitoring costs $400–$900 in hardware plus $600–$1,500 in monitoring over 5 years — totaling $1,000–$2,400. The owned system costs 30–40% less over the same period.',
