      shortDef: 'A one-time charge collected by a security company when starting a new monitoring service to cover account setup, equipment programming, and initial cellular registration.',
      fullDef: 'Activation fees are one-time charges collected when a monitoring service begins. For professionally installed systems, the activation fee (also called a start-up fee or connection fee) typically runs $25–$99 and covers account creation in the monitoring center\'s system, programming the panel to communicate with that center, and registering the cellular communicator on the carrier network.\n\nFor DIY systems, activation is often free or nominal ($0–$10) because the homeowner self-installs and self-programs via an app. Some companies waive activation fees as a promotion during sales periods or for customers who bundle multiple services (home automation, video, monitoring together).\n\nActivation fees are often negotiable, particularly for high-value customers signing multi-year contracts. Always ask for a fee waiver before agreeing to terms; companies routinely accommodate this request rather than lose a contract sale.',
