      fullDef: 'Security monitoring cancellation fees are among the most litigated issues in the industry. The standard formula is 75–100% of the remaining monthly monitoring fees for the unexpired contract term. A homeowner who cancels a 36-month, $45/month contract after 12 months owes 75% × 24 months × $45 = $810 under a typical 75% clause.\n\nSome states have enacted specific protections: California limits cancellation fees to 1 month\'s charge after the first year of service; other states require 30-day written notice with no penalty after the initial term. Federal FTC regulations require clear disclosure of cancellation terms before signing.\n\nStrategies to avoid cancellation fees include transferring the contract to the new homeowner when selling a property (many companies allow this), relocating the service to a new address (relocation policies vary widely), or negotiating a goodwill termination if service has been poor. Document all service complaints in writing as leverage for a fee waiver.',
