      fullDef: 'Homeowner\'s insurance discounts for security systems reflect the statistically lower claim frequency and severity at monitored homes. The Insurance Information Institute estimates that homes with monitored security systems have 60% fewer burglary claims than unmonitored homes. Insurers translate this risk reduction into premium discounts that vary by company and coverage type.\n\nDiscount tiers typically reflect the level of protection: a basic smoke detector might yield 2–3%; adding deadbolt locks adds another 2%; a monitored burglar alarm system adds 5–10%; a full monitored system (fire, carbon monoxide, burglary, medical alert) with UL-listed monitoring can add 15–20%. Discounts are applied to the theft and fire portions of the premium, not the full policy amount.\n\nTo claim the discount, insurers typically require a certificate from the monitoring company confirming 24/7 monitoring service, the UL listing of the monitoring center, and sometimes the type of communication (cellular is preferred). Annual monitoring certificates must be resubmitted when the policy renews.',
