      slug: 'obd-ii-codes',
      letter: 'O',
      shortDef: 'Standardized diagnostic trouble codes stored by your vehicle\'s computer when a fault is detected â€” readable by any OBD-II scanner for $25â€“$150 to identify problems before expensive diagnosis.',
      fullDef: 'OBD-II (On-Board Diagnostics, second generation) is the standardized vehicle diagnostic system mandated in all cars sold in the US after 1996. When a sensor detects a problem, the car\'s ECU stores a Diagnostic Trouble Code (DTC) and illuminates the Check Engine Light. Codes follow a standard format: P (powertrain), B (body), C (chassis), or U (network), followed by four digits. P0420 (catalytic converter efficiency below threshold) and P0300 (random misfire) are two of the most common.\n\nReading codes requires an OBD-II scanner, available from AutoZone or O\'Reilly for free (loan-a-tool programs) or purchased for $25â€“$150. Advanced scanners show live sensor data, freeze frame data at the moment of fault, and pending codes not yet triggering the light. The code alone tells you what the computer detected, not necessarily what\'s broken â€” P0420 could mean a failed catalytic converter ($800â€“$1,800), an oxygen sensor ($150â€“$400), or an exhaust leak. Proper diagnosis requires interpreting the code in context.\n\nNever buy a used vehicle without checking stored and pending codes via an OBD-II scanner. A cleared Check Engine Light still has pending codes if the issue is active â€” they resurface within 1â€“3 drive cycles. A pre-purchase OBD scan is free at AutoZone and takes two minutes. Discover a P0301 (cylinder 1 misfire) before signing paperwork and you have negotiating leverage; discover it three days later and it\'s your problem.',
      example: 'A buyer runs an OBD-II scan on a 2017 Ford Escape at AutoZone before purchase. He finds a cleared P0171 (system lean, Bank 1) and a pending P0174 (system lean, Bank 2) â€” classic symptoms of a failing PCV system or vacuum leak. He negotiates $1,200 off the asking price and has the $340 repair done immediately after purchase.',
