      shortDef: 'A company that collects personal information from public records, loyalty programs, social media, and other sources, then sells or licenses that data to third parties.',
      fullDef: 'The data broker industry generates over $200 billion annually in the US according to FTC estimates. Major brokersâ€”Acxiom, LexisNexis, Experian, CoreLogic, Intelius, Spokeo, BeenVerifiedâ€”compile profiles containing hundreds of data points on virtually every American adult: home address history, estimated income, property ownership, marital status, political affiliation inferences, purchasing behaviors, health condition inferences, social media activity, and professional history. Sources include public records, voter registration files, DMV data (in states that permit it), credit header data, store loyalty programs, and app location data purchases.\n\nData brokers sell to: marketers (targeted advertising), employers (background screening), landlords (tenant screening), insurers (risk underwriting), debt collectors, bail bondsmen, and increasingly, law enforcement. A 2022 investigation found that US law enforcement agencies purchased location data from brokers to circumvent warrant requirements. Stalkers and domestic abusers have used broker lookup sites to locate victims.\n\nRemoving yourself from data brokers is tedious but feasible. Each broker has its own opt-out process, typically requiring email, mail, or form submission with ID verification. Services like DeleteMe ($129/year), Privacy Bee, and Kanary automate opt-outs across 200+ brokers and re-submit every few months since data re-populates. Opting out of all major brokers takes 8â€“20 hours of manual work or an ongoing paid service.',
      example: 'A journalist researching their own data broker profile discovers that Spokeo shows their current home address, phone number, estimated home value ($340,000), full name of spouse, and names of relativesâ€”all available to anyone who pays $3.95 for a search. They use DeleteMe to remove listings from 35 broker sites over a three-month period.',
