      fullDef: 'Employee Assistance Programs are offered by approximately 97% of large US employers (500+ employees) and 75% of mid-size employers (100â€“500 employees), yet utilization rates average only 4â€“6% of eligible employees per yearâ€”meaning most workers leave a significant free benefit unused. A standard EAP provides 6â€“8 free counseling sessions per "presenting issue" per year; some employers offer 12 sessions. Sessions are provided by EAP-contracted therapists, typically within 3â€“5 business days for non-emergency appointments.\n\nEAPs are managed by vendors like Lyra Health, Spring Health, Optum, Cigna Behavioral Health, and Magellan. Newer EAPs (Lyra, Spring) include unlimited coaching sessions, digital mental health tools, and same-week psychiatry access alongside traditional counseling. Lyra Health has demonstrated 3.6Ã— ROI in employer cost reduction through reduced medical utilization and absenteeism in independent studies.\n\nEAP sessions are confidential from the employer: the employer pays a per-employee per-month fee ($15â€“$40 typically) and receives only aggregate utilization dataâ€”no names, presenting issues, or session content. EAP coverage does not affect your health insurance benefits or deductible. After EAP sessions are exhausted, the EAP typically facilitates a referral to ongoing in-network care. Smart sequence: exhaust EAP sessions first, then transition to insurance-covered care, minimizing out-of-pocket cost.',
